In any project, go to the project summary page and select the Statistics view.  Click the All Issues link (or Unresolved, or Added Recently, or any of the links in that section of the page), and you'll wind up on a issues search page with no results, and wide open search criteria (Project: all, Type: all, etc.).  This appears to be due to the fact that the query strings in the URLs for these links are wrong.  For example, the URL for the Added Recently link is 

{noformat}
/issues/?&jqlQuery=project+%3D+MCCORE+AND+created%3E%3D-1w+ORDER+BY+created+DESC
{noformat}

The leading & character is wrong, and the parameter name appears to be wrong, too.  This modified query string

{noformat}
issues/?jql=project+%3D+MCCORE+AND+created%3E%3D-1w+ORDER+BY+created+DESC
{noformat}

works correctly.

