In the restricted functions documentation for Cloud it is never mentioned that you can only use the standard ports when configuring an inbound mail server either in JIRA or in JIRA Service Desk.

This is because our SOCK proxy is configured to only allow below ports:
- IMAP: 143
- IMAPS: 993
- POP3: 110
- POP3S: 995



This is actually mentioned in a comment from George Barnett on [Outbound connectivity: should we keep our current squid+SOCKS layer 7 proxy design, identify an improved layer 7 proxy design, or transition to NAT?|https://extranet.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=2471665094&focusedCommentId=2471408313#comment-2471408313]

{quote}
On the socks 5 server side of things, set a simple whitelist of allowed ports.  This will mean that in the event of a compromise we won't become a botnet host.......
{quote}

